					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Indium Tin Oxide (ITO) coated glass is a type of glass that has been coated with a thin layer of ITO, a compound that provides the glass with electrical conductivity while maintaining its transparency. This makes it ideal for use in touchscreen displays, such as those found on cell phones. ITO glass is utilized across various industries, including medical, military, research and development, automobile, aviation, and technology. Its unique properties of optical transparency and electrical conductivity make it a key material in the production of touchscreens and other cutting-edge technologies.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">铟锡氧化物（ITO）涂层玻璃是一种涂有ITO薄层的玻璃，ITO是一种在保持玻璃透明度的同时为玻璃提供导电性的化合物。这使得它非常适合用于触摸屏显示器，例如手机上的触摸屏显示器。ITO玻璃应用于各个行业，包括医疗、军事、研发、汽车、航空和技术。其独特的光学透明性和导电性使其成为触摸屏和其他尖端技术生产的关键材料。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>In2O3(SnO2)</sumFormula>
